# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // 2π (full circle in radians)
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √(1/2)

// Configuration
var config = {
  repulsion: 4000,
  springConstant: 0.004,
  decay: 0.92,
  centerGravity: 0.0003,
  maxParticleCount: 40,
  friction: 0.04,
  rate: 0.06
};

// Define nodes (graph vertices)
var nodes = [
  { id: 'hub',     label: 'Hub',     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'alpha',   label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'beta',    label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'gamma',   label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'delta',   label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Define edges (springs between nodes)
var edges = [
  { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state (current and target)
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle system
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function physicsStep() {
  // 1. Node-to-node REPULSION (Coulomb's law style)
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      var force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);
      var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2. Spring ATTRACTION along edges (Hooke's law)
  for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
    var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
    var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
    var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
    var force = (edges[e].k || config.springConstant) * displacement;
    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3. Center GRAVITY + velocity decay + position update
  for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
    nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.centerGravity;
    nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.centerGravity;
    nodes[n].vx *= config.decay;
    nodes[n].vy *= config.decay;
    nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
    nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
  }
}

// Spawn a particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.maxParticleCount) return;
  var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;
  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
  });
}

// Update all particles
function updateParticles() {
  for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    var p = particles[i];
    p.age++;
    p.vx *= 1 - config.friction * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.friction * 0.125;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}

// Smooth camera follow
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.rate;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.rate;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.rate;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
  physicsStep();
  updateCamera();
  updateParticles();
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** with a particle system. Specifically:

### 🔵 Graph Layout (Force-Directed)
- **6 nodes** ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") are connected by **8 edges**
- Nodes **repel** each other (like electric charges — inverse square law)
- Connected nodes are pulled together by **springs** (Hooke's law with rest lengths)
- A gentle **center gravity** pulls everything toward (400, 300)
- **Velocity decay** (0.92) prevents infinite acceleration

### ✨ Particle Effects
- Every 3 frames, a particle spawns from a random node
- Particles drift outward in random directions with friction
- They die after 800–2000 frames (max 40 alive at once)
- This creates a subtle ambient "energy" visual effect

### 🎥 Smooth Camera
- Camera position lerps toward a target at 6% per frame

### ⏱️ Runs at ~60 FPS
- `setInterval(tick, 16)` drives the simulation

**In short: it's the physics engine for an animated node graph visualization with decorative floating particles — likely rendered elsewhere by a drawing/canvas function not included here.**
